lead_paragraph: England captain Eoin Morgan blamed his team's defeat in Sunday's World Twenty20 final on the batsmen, saying they were 40 runs short of what could have been a winning total.

headline.print_headline: England Captain Morgan Rues Below-Par Score in Windies Loss
